Q: How to change time according to TimeZone? A: <p>Well if you have a <code>Date.now()</code> stored in a <code>const</code> then you can just convert it to your local time with Date property and then just convert it to American standard time by changing the timezone.</p>
<p><div class="snippet" data-lang="js" data-hide="false" data-console="true" data-babel="false" data-babel-preset-react="false" data-babel-preset-ts="false">
<div class="snippet-code">
<pre class="snippet-code-js lang-js prettyprint-override"><code>const LocalTime = new Date(Date.now());
const AmericanTime = LocalTime.toLocaleString("en-US", {
    timeZone: "America/New_York",
});

console.log (AmericanTime); // console log the particular date in american time</code></pre>
